Job_Description:
Nature of Position
The City is seeking a Network Analyst with municipal or government information systems experience to fill our open Network Analyst (IT Systems Analyst) position within the IT Department. The work requires comprehensive knowledge of computer network systems, routing and switching technologies, VoIP/telephony systems and firewall technologies, data gathering, integration and maintenance, IT project management, experience in network operations and troubleshooting, and strong leadership and analytical skills.

As a member of the IT team, the successful candidate will:
Coordinate with various departments to perform computer network enhancements and resolve a variety of network related issues;
Perform complex analysis in the development, operation, and administration of the City’s information networks;
In addition to meeting the established employment standards, the ideal candidate will thrive in a fast paced environment; be able to multitask and think creatively when problem-solving; be a team leader and facilitator; have experience designing, developing, and evaluating network systems and related communications. Knowledge of cloud computing is highly desirable.

